										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Here&#8217;s a wonderful poem that my good friend JaniceT wrote about our darling Twist! JaniceT is a fantastic poetess who writes in Neo-Victorian style. Please, shower her with thanks and praise for this lovely little piece!</p>
<p>Twist</p>
<p>A slender man ignores the damp,<br />
That permeates an upper room,<br />
With not but an old oil lamp<br />
To keep at bay the London gloom.</p>
<p>His fixed intent and form are bent<br />
Upon the timepiece in his hand.<br />
Small tools he plies to this device<br />
With more than skill at his command.</p>
<p>Soon comes a sigh to signify<br />
That his repairs are now complete.<br />
He notes the face but not the time<br />
And takes another sip of tea.</p>
<p>JaniceT</p>
<p><a href="http://janice-t.weebly.com/" target="_blank">Read other poetry by JaniceT here</a></p>
